pull_request.title: Deprecate cms-strapi
pull_request.body:
Deprecates `cms-strapi` as it relies on [Heroku, whose free plans are being shut down](https://blog.heroku.com/next-chapter). The README now links to [Strapi’s official demo application](https://github.com/strapi/foodadvisor/). The README format follows [the deprecated `blog-starter-typescript` example](https://github.com/vercel/next.js/tree/canary/examples/blog-starter-typescript).

This change was discussed with the Strapi team.

issue.title: Open Permalink on GitHub for fails on 0.54.1 but works on 0.54 (Unauthenticated)
issue.body:
### Background

- I have **NOT** signed into GitHub with this extension.
  - This is because I'm using this extension only to open GitHub permalinks quickly, and for this functionality, I hadn't needed to do sign in.
- I haven't changed any configuration settings for this extension. 
- Each of repository has `https://github.com/[...]/[...].git` as its `origin` remote.

### Steps to Reproduce

- On 0.54.1, "Open Permalink on GitHub" results in the following error:
  - `Command 'GitHub Issues: Open Permalink on GitHub' resulted in an error (file://... has no GitHub remotes)`
- If I downgrade to 0.54.0, "Open Permalink on GitHub" works correctly.
- This is happening in every repository I tested, including a fresh one I downloaded from GitHub.

### Versions

- Extension version: 0.54.1 / 0.54.0
- VSCode Version: 1.73.1
- OS: macOS 13.0
